# FE-BE Integration Contract Rules
Description: Frontend-backend integration contract and environment alignment.

## Base URL & Prefix
- **Backend base**: `http://localhost:8080/api` (server context-path `/api`)
- **Frontend env**: use `VITE_API_URL` (fallback `VITE_API_BASE_URL`)

## Endpoint Versioning
- All public APIs use `/v1/*` (e.g., `/v1/actions`, `/v1/metrics`, `/v1/reports`, `/v1/onboarding`)

## Social Login (Spec)
- OAuth2 Authorization Code + PKCE
- Endpoints: `GET /v1/auth/oauth/{provider}/authorize`, `POST /v1/auth/oauth/{provider}/callback`

## Response & Error Shape
- All APIs return `ApiResponse<T>` with `success`, `message`, `data`, `timestamp`
- FE must handle `401` by redirecting to `/login` and triggering refresh flow once

## Logging & Masking
- Follow `LOGGING_GUIDE.md` for request/response logging and masking rules
- Never log raw tokens or passwords from either FE or BE
